RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO ANGELS stalked from outside going four wide into the turn, asked for run by the quarter pole, struck the lead by mid-stretch and was kept busy to the wire. COZZOLANI was coaxed forward inside but outpaced early, chased from along the rail, put to urging leaving the turn, made a bid in mid-stretch but was outfinished. SCRAPPY PATCH was urged at the break but lacking early speed, swung six wide into the stretch, kept on to get up for show. SHAWK'S LIL AVA pursued the pace three to four wide, moved out five deep at the top of the stretch, was outfinished for show honors. SHE'S A PLAYER set the pace racing off the rail, moved clear leaving the backstretch, faltered in upper stretch and faded. BONANZA GRADE pressed the pace between runners three deep, dropped back two to three wide between runners on the turn and came up empty.

ENTRY.NAME: Cozzolani
ENTRY.COMMENT: coaxed forward inside, chased, inside bid mid-str, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: She's a Player
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace off rail, clear 7/16, faltered, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Scrappy Patch
ENTRY.COMMENT: urged brk, no speed, swung 6w, up for show

ENTRY.NAME: Two Angels
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside, 4wide turn, ask by 1/4, led by 1/8, kept busy

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 15600. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEADEDTOTHESTARS set the pace racing just off the rail in the clear, was engaged by an outside foe up the backstretch, was overtaken narrowly midway on the turn, dueled inside that rival retaking the lead by mid-stretch, held that rival and just lasted from a fast-closing other foe. HUNTER'S LEGACY was coaxed forward after the start in pursuit of the leader, moved up outside that one to press from the half-mile marker, bid at the five-sixteenths taking a narrow lead, dueled outside into upper stretch, lost the lead to the dueling partner at that juncture and was outkicked but kept on to just save the place. J B'S LEGACY settled tracking inside just off the leaders, came out three deep in the stretch for room, surged too late and missed while finishing best of all. CATALE STORM stalked from outside going four wide on the turn, ran on evenly. RONALD DALE got away alertly, stalked from inside another rival going three wide into the turn, moved out five wide at the top of the stretch, was not a late threat. CHARING CROSS lacked early speed racing near inside, came out six wide for the drive, failed to menace. OUR CORNERSTONE was fractious in the gate, lacked early speed, swung six wide, made no bids.

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, came out 3w str, surged too late

ENTRY.COMMENT: forward, press 1/2, bid 5/16, duel, outkicked, just lasted place

ENTRY.NAME: Charing Cross
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, near inside, came out 6w upper str, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Our Cornerstone
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, no speed, swung 6w, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Headedtothestars
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace off rail, dueled, headed, regained command, just held

ENTRY.NAME: Ronald Dale
ENTRY.COMMENT: away alertly, 3w pursuit, moved out 5w, no late threat

ENTRY.NAME: Catale Storm
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked outside, 4w turn, kept on evenly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CON SUERTE was very reluctant to load, raced unhurriedly at the rear dropping a ways back of the leaders, steadily advanced coming out a bit to pass a rival on the far turn then back nearer the rail, rallied inside and edged clear. FREE SPIRITED engaged outside a rival dueling two wide, dispatched that rival but was then joined by an outside foe dueling while just off the rail into and on the far turn, lugged out about the eighth pole, was overtaken but second best. WITSEC was within range racing mostly three wide, lost some ground on the far turn, moved out five wide coming into upper stretch, kicked on to get up for show honors. LISA G stalked from outside, engaged the leader three to four wide to force the issue coming to the half, could not keep up with that one into upper stretch and was forced out near the furlong marker, lacked the needed late kick. RED RIVER WITCH stalked just off the leaders going three to five wide throughout and failed to rally. MISS CANEY dueled briefly inside, dropped back and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Con Suerte
ENTRY.COMMENT: very reluctant, unhurried, steady advance, rail bid, clear

ENTRY.NAME: Witsec
ENTRY.OWNER: Ullery Bloodstock LLC Scott Young Racing LLC and Rags Racing Stable LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: mostly 3wide, moved out 5w into str, up for show

ENTRY.NAME: Lisa G
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked outside, 3-4w, forced out 1/8, no kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUSTANGMAGNA dueled outside a rival two to three wide early, dispatched that rival then was engaged by an outside foe dueling inside that one briefly, edged clear and held sway under steady handling. MY GOLDEN PRIZE settled off the pace, fanned six wide into upper stretch, ran on to get up for second. MAREBELL stalked the leaders going four to five wide, was outfinished for place. PICAFLOR was encouraged forward from the start, dueled inside, dropped back heading to the turn, kept on in the stretch. GOTOTHEWINDOW raced near the inside last but one into the turn, failed to menace. PREACH IT GIRL pressed the leading pair from outside three to four wide, engaged the leader in a brief duel on the turn, came up empty for the drive. SURE WASN'T ME broke a step slowly and was outpaced.

ENTRY.NAME: Mustangmagna

Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A M ile Or Over Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CADI DEVILLE dueled inside a rival early, edged clear leaving the backstretch racing in the two path on the far turn, held rivals at bay under moderate but steady urging. TIFFANY TWIST stalked from outside mostly four to five wide, kept on in the stretch and won the battle for place. SMOKIN' OKIE angled in early, saved ground through the first turn and the far turn advancing inside foes in upper stretch but coming off the fence, kept on but missed second. BRODIE BABY was urged at the break, pressed the pace three to four wide, lacked the needed late kick. EUTYCHIA settled off the pace two to three wide, came out for the drive, failed to menace. KIMBELL'S STRATEGY raced at the rear three to four wide, failed to menace. JUST ROSIE dueled briefly two to three wide outside the eventual winner, steadily weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCESS BALL stalked the pace, took closer order four wide on the turn, struck the lead in mid-stretch, edged clear inside the final sixteenth. CATALE WINEMIXER pressed outside early, went three wide on the turn taking a narrow lead at the five-sixteenths, was clear in upper stretch but outkicked. HANNAH FO FANNAH pressed from inside, dropped back, came out for the stretch run, failed to rally. LITTLE RIVER JEWEL was off a bit slowly and awkwardly then steadied slightly after the start, raced at the rear inside, went evenly and made no bid. KAVACHI tracked in behind the leaders, came out five wide for the stretch run, had no rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 86. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022-2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $7,500. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BROTHER AARON settled at the rear, fanned five wide leaving the turn, drifted in a bit in upper stretch engaging the leader, took over by the furlong marker and held that inside rival while being taken. HUNTER QUICK moved forward with mild encouragement to take the lead after the opening furlong, was clear outside the three-eighths racing in the two path, overtaken in mid-stretch but kept on gamely to be second best. MAGIC CARPET stalked off the leaders mid-pack racing four to six wide, ran along for show. SECRET BLARNEY pressed three wide, weakened. SPANISH HOMBRE broke a bit slowly, moved up inside, failed to menace. EXCITING pressed outside four wide, weakened. TARUCA was not a factor racing off the inside.

ENTRY.NAME: Hunter Quick
ENTRY.COMMENT: forward, led after 1/8, clear outside 3/8, 2path, kept on gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Brother Aaron
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, fanned 5w, drifted in, led 1/8, held foe

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Purse 30000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROWDY RIVER was pressured early then moved clear up the backstretch setting the pace inside, drew off in the stretch while being kept to the task and held safe. BECKETT'S LUCKYDAY tucked in moving from three to two wide on the first turn to track in behind the leaders inside foes in the second flight but just off the rail, gained the place inside of. KODALINE , who pressed the winner early racing two to three wide, dropped back into the far turn but kept on in the stretch to secure show honors. FRIGERATOR was caught seven then six wide on the first turn, advanced outside foes up the backstretch to stalk, moved nearer to just off the flank of the leader three wide midway on the far turn, could not sustain the effort. LEGIONARY moved in from six to five wide on the first turn, moved in a bit further racing off the leaders up the backstretch and dropping back into the far turn, moved five wide nearing the quarter pole, failed to rally but improved position. BRIGGSEY stalked three to four wide racing between rivals in the second flight up the backstretch, weakened. CHEROKEE LEGACY raced four to five wide on the turns and faded in the stretch. MORHAWK broke awkwardly and slowly and was outpaced.

ENTRY.NAME: Rowdy River
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressured early, clear, pace inside, drew off, kept task, safe

ENTRY.NAME: Beckett's Luckyday
ENTRY.OWNER: Swan Patrick E and Lewis Robert E
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3w early, tracked in behind, inside-2path, gained place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKPORT KAT tucked in behind the leaders in the three to four path rating off those, was in just a bit tight on heels early up the backstretch, made a swift move four wide between rivals past the five-sixteenths to bid coming to the quarter pole, was in command by the top of the stretch, drove clear and held safe. JACKS SPRING BREAK tracked inside just off the leaders to the top of the stretch, angled out in upper stretch, kicked on well to share the place with KWIK, who stalked in the two to three path early, moved out to advance four wide between runners early on the far turn, switched outside the leader in upper stretch, ran on to share second. NEEDABETTERJOCK set the pace racing just off the rail facing early pressure from an outside rival, was overtaken by the top of the stretch, kept on till mid-stretch then yielded. CHOCOLATEICECREAM got away slowly, shifted in racing in the two to three path toward the rear early, came out for the drive and improved position. TOAH was caught five wide on the first turn forwardly-positioned, was within range six wide on the far turn but had no late kick. WILLY SPECIAL CATS was a tad rank heading into the first turn, shifted in to race near the inside, failed to menace. WIN FOR FUN was fractious in the gate, raced up close four to five wide, faded. MAYFAIR HEIGHTS pressed three wide, faltered and faded. WAVERUNNER failed to threaten while racing several paths off the inside. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION OPENING QUARTER-MILE FRACTION WAS UNAVAILABLE. FRACTION ADDED UPON REVIEW.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, angled out upper, shared place

ENTRY.COMMENT: off slowly, shifted in, 2-3path, came out, improved

ENTRY.NAME: Willy Special Cats
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit rank early, shifted in, near inside, no menace

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 10 6F Dirt CR: 67. Allowance Purse 27600. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GYPSY ROSE settled off the pace, saved ground mid-pack on the turn, rallied inside in the stretch striking the lead about seventy yards from home and edged away. STORMY BISONETTE moved clear and shifted in, set the pace in the two path, faced pressure from outside foes into and on the turn, was clear in upper stretch but outkicked while second best. CANDY'S A DANDY stalked from outside going four wide into the turn and in range of the leader, loomed a threat but ran on evenly and lacked the needed late kick while keeping on well enough to capture show honors. SURE SHOT SHELLY moved forward outside the leader to press that one three wide into the turn, contended between foes on the turn, was outkicked in the lane. SMART OKIE raced off the pace near but just off the rail, ran evenly and made no bid while improving position. GOSPEL MOLLY pursued from outside mid-pack, was asked for more while five wide coming to the quarter pole and within striking distance but evened out. MISSWISH was ridden along racing off the inside, failed to menace. TOM'S GIRL moved off the rail, was never near enough to threaten. ALWAYS BE DANCIN was well back early, swung five wide into upper stretch and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Gypsy Rose
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, saved ground, rallied inside, led 70yds

ENTRY.NAME: Stormy Bisonette
ENTRY.COMMENT: moved clear, pace, 2path, clear, outkicked, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Candy's a Dandy
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, outside, 4wide turn, in range, evenly, no kick
